  "body": "\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Oral care is not cosmetic upkeep. It is <strong>health discipline</strong>, <strong>social credibility</strong>, and <strong>professional readiness</strong> expressed through daily habits.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">In meetings, interviews, presentations, negotiations, and teamwork, you speak at close range. The condition of your teeth and breath directly shapes how others perceive your hygiene, discipline, and confidence.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">1) First Impressions Begin Before You Speak</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-11 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"/images/img-614.jpg\" alt=\"Image\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.diyherbaltea.com/images/storing-mint-in-water.jpg\" alt=\"Image\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"/images/img-612.jpg\" alt=\"Image\" style=\"width:538px;height:auto\"/></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">People subconsciously register:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Clean teeth</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Healthy gums</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Fresh breath</li>\n\n\n\n<li>A confident smile</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Neglected oral care silently signals carelessness. Fresh breath and clean teeth signal discipline and self-respect.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">2) What Causes Mouth Odor (Halitosis)</h2>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Persistent mouth odor is usually due to bacterial activity:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Food particles between teeth</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Plaque along the gumline</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Tongue coating</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Gum inflammation</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Cavities</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Dry mouth</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p 